<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030508>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 12. Gracilentulus europaeus Szeptycki from Rishiri Is., Hokkaido.A) dorsal view of thoraces I–II, left side; B) dorsal view of abdominal segments V–VII, right side; C) dorsal view of abdominal segment VIII, left side; D) abdominal sternites II–III; E) posterior part of abdominal sternite V; F) ventral view of abdominal segment VI; G) ventral view of abdominal segment VII. A, E–G, female (NSMT-Ap 561); B, D, female (NSMT-Ap 563); C, female (NSMT-Ap 562). Abbreviations: al, anterolateral pore; lt, laterotergal pore; psm, posterosubmedial pore; sl, sublateral pore; spsm, sternal posterosubmedial pore. Scale bar: 20 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5030508/files/figure.png" .

