<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030506>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 11. Gracilentulus europaeus Szeptycki from Rishiri Is., Hokkaido. A) head, dorsal view; B) maxillary palpus; C) labial palpus; D) canal of maxillary gland; E) pseudoculus; F) exterior view of foretarsus; G) interior view of foretarsus; H) abdominal appendage II; I) female squama genitalis. A–G, female (NSMT-Ap 561), H–I, female (NSMT-Ap 562). Abbreviations: fp, frontal pore; D, dorsal sensillum; V, ventral sensillum. Arrows indicate pores. Scale bars: 20 μm for A, F, G; 10 μm for other images." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5030506/files/figure.png" .

